{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845689001,"sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6bad8001e3fyGFcgcpAbtt","messageID":"msg_d78a6a34f0012yskB0YhP0Wfxa","sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2718e5c3e93e4e79b54f4123","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n18:   - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n19:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n20:   - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CreateSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n23:   - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxName` (string), `EntryPoints` ([]SandboxEntryPoint)\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Path`, `Protocol`, `Endpoint` (all string)\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define context keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go`\n29:   - Keys: `contextKeyUserToken`, `contextKeyServiceAccount`, `contextKeyServiceAccountName`, `contextKeyNamespace`\n30: \n31: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n32:   - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), label/annotation keys\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: Infrastructure Components\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `sandboxCreator` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go`\n37:   - Fields: `k8sClient`, `sandboxController`, `storeClient`, `publicKey`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `createSandbox()` method for `sandboxCreator`\n40:   - Steps: register watcher → store placeholder → create CR → wait (2min) → resolve IP → update store\n41:   - Rollback on failure: delete CR + delete store entry\n42:   - Use independent 30s timeout context for rollback delete\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `resolvePodIP()` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n45:   - Priority: sandbox name → annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` → informer cache → label selector\n46:   - Require PodRunning phase and non-empty PodIP\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `buildEntryPoints()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n49:   - Input: podIP, []TargetPort\n50:   - Output: []SandboxEntryPoint with format `host:port`\n51: \n52: ### Phase 3: Workload Builders\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `buildSandboxObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n55:   - Input: *AgentRuntime, sessionID\n56:   - Name format: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n57:   - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n58:   - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n59:   - Copy podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n60:   - Set replicas=1, lifecycle.shutdownTime=now+MaxSessionDuration\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n63:   - For CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n64:   - Minimal metadata, no full PodSpec\n65:   - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n66: \n67: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement AuthMode injection for CodeInterpreter\n68:   - If AuthMode=picod and publicKey available: inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n69:   - Support optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n70: \n71: ### Phase 4: HTTP Handlers\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `handleAgentRuntimeCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n74:   - Parse JSON → set Kind=AgentRuntime → Validate()\n75:   - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n76:   - Check podTemplate non-nil\n77:   - Call createSandbox()\n78:   - Return CreateSandboxResponse (200) or error\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/code_interpreter.go`\n81:   - Similar to AgentRuntime but:\n82:   - Kind=CodeInterpreter\n83:   - Support WarmPoolSize > 0 → buildSandboxClaimObject()\n84:   - Support AuthMode (picod/none)\n85:   - Default ports: [{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}] if spec.Ports empty\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Register routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n88:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime → handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n89:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n90:   - POST /v1/code-interpreter → handleCodeInterpreterCreate\n91:   - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `handleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n94:   - Load session from store by sessionId\n95:   - NotFound → 404 with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n96:   - Delete SandboxClaim if Kind=SandboxClaim, else delete Sandbox\n97:   - API NotFound on delete → treat as success\n98:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID from store\n99:   - Return 200 `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`\n100: \n101: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n102: \n103: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Define error constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` or `pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`\n104:   - ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound, ErrTemplateMissing, ErrPublicKeyMissing\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement error mapping in handlers\n107:   - JSON bind失败 → 400 `Invalid request body`\n108:   - Validate 失败 → 400 `<field> is required`\n109:   - Template missing → 400 with `pod template` in message\n110:   - NotFound from informer → 404 `agent runtime not found` / `code interpreter not found`\n111:   - Auth失败 → 401 from authMiddleware\n112:   - Timeout/internal → 500 `internal server error`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement rollback strategy in `createSandbox()`\n115:   - CR 创建前失败: delete store placeholder\n116:   - CR 创建后超时: delete CR (30s timeout) + delete store\n117:   - Pod IP 解析失败: delete CR + delete store\n118:   - Store 更新失败: log warning, CR left for GC\n119: \n120: ### Phase 6: Integration\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Integrate with `client-go` typed clients\n123:   - Use `AgentRuntimeInterface` and `CodeInterpreterInterface` for reading templates\n124:   - Use informers + listers for cached reads\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Integrate with dynamic client\n127:   - Create Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs using `dynamic.Interface`\n128:   - GVR: `SandboxGVR`, `SandboxClaimGVR`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Integrate with SandboxReconciler\n131:   - Call `WatchSandboxOnce(ns, name)` before CR creation\n132:   - Wait on channel with 2min timeout\n133:   - Receive notification when status=running\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Integrate with Store\n136:   - StoreSandbox() with placeholder before CR create\n137:   - UpdateSandbox() with full info after IP resolution\n138:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID() on rollback or delete\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Integrate with authMiddleware\n141:   - When EnableAuth=true: use per-user dynamic client from `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient`\n142:   - Cache key: `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n143: \n144: ### Phase 7: Testing (TDD)\n145: \n146: #### Unit Tests\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go`\n149:   - Valid request → no error\n150:   - Empty name → error contains `name is required`\n151:   - Empty namespace → error contains `namespace is required`\n152:   - Invalid kind → error contains `kind is required`\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success` (TestCase-WM-001)\n155:   - Given: valid AgentRuntime in informer cache\n156:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime with valid JSON\n157:   - Then: 200, response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n158:   - Use fake clientset + mock store + mock SandboxReconciler\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Idempotent` (TestCase-WM-002)\n161:   - Given: two consecutive requests with same name\n162:   - When: first creation succeeds\n163:   - Then: second returns same sessionId\n164: \n165: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate` (TestCase-WM-003)\n166:   - Given: AgentRuntime with spec.podTemplate=nil\n167:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime\n168:   - Then: 400, message contains `pod template`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_WarmPool`\n171:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n172:   - When: POST /v1/code-interpreter\n173:   - Then: creates SandboxClaim, response Kind=SandboxClaim\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_DefaultPorts`\n176:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with empty spec.Ports\n177:   - When: creation succeeds\n178:   - Then: entryPoints contains default 8080/HTTP\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModePicoD`\n181:   - Given: AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n182:   - When: sandbox created\n183:   - Then: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var injected\n184: \n185: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModeNone`\n186:   - Given: AuthMode=none\n187:   - When: sandbox created\n188:   - Then: no PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var\n189: \n190: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCreateSandbox_Timeout`\n191:   - Given: no running notification within 2min\n192:   - When: createSandbox() waits\n193:   - Then: error `sandbox creation timed out`, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n194: \n195: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestCreateSandbox_RollbackOnIPResolutionFailure`\n196:   - Given: pod IP resolution fails\n197:   - When: createSandbox() attempts to resolve\n198:   - Then: CR deleted, store entry deleted, error returned\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromAnnotation`\n201:   - Given: Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n202:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n203:   - Then: uses annotated pod name\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromOwnerReference`\n206:   - Given: pods listed by label, one has owner reference Kind=Sandbox\n207:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n208:   - Then: selects pod with matching owner reference\n209: \n210: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestResolvePodIP_PodNotRunning`\n211:   - Given: pod in Pending/Failed phase\n212:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n213:   - Then: error indicating pod not running\n214: \n215: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestBuildSandboxObject_LabelsAndAnnotations`\n216:   - Given: AgentRuntime with sessionTimeout\n217:   - When: buildSandboxObject() called\n218:   - Then: labels and annotations set correctly\n219: \n220: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestBuildSandboxClaimObject_MinimalMetadata`\n221:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n222:   - When: buildSandboxClaimObject() called\n223:   - Then: minimal metadata, no PodSpec\n224: \n225: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success`\n226:   - Given: session exists in store\n227:   - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n228:   - Then: 200, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n229: \n230: - [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (Spec requirement)\n231:   - Given: no session key in store\n232:   - When: DELETE invoked\n233:   - Then: 404, message contains session id\n234: \n235: #### Test Infrastructure\n236: \n237: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `testEnv` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go`\n238:   - Fields: k8sClient, reconciler, store, server, redis (miniredis), fakeClient, dynamicClient\n239: \n240: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Implement `newTestEnv(t *testing.T)` function\n241:   - Start miniredis\n242:   - Create fake clientset with registered AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n243:   - Create fake dynamic client\n244:   - Initialize K8sClient, SandboxReconciler, Store\n245:   - Build Server (auth/TLS disabled)\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock implementations\n248:   - MockWorkloadManager interface\n249:   - Mock SandboxReconciler.WatchSandboxOnce returning controllable channel\n250: \n251: #### Integration Tests\n252: \n253: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox`\n254:   - Deploy AgentCube (Helm install to Kind cluster)\n255:   - Create ServiceAccount and get token\n256:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime\n257:   - Verify response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n258:   - Access sandbox via entryPoint to verify connectivity\n259:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId to cleanup\n260: \n261: - [ ] **TEST-031**: E2E fixture `echo_agent.yaml`\n262:   - Simple echo server AgentRuntime definition\n263: \n264: #### Coverage Verification\n265: \n266: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n267:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n268:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n269:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n270: \n271: ### Phase 8: Documentation\n272: \n273: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n274:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/agent-runtime\n275:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/code-interpreter\n276: \n277: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n278:   - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n279: \n280: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update pkg/workloadmanager/README.md\n281:   - Architecture diagram\n282:   - Component interaction flow\n283:   - Configuration options\n284: \n285: ## Acceptance Criteria\n286: \n287: - [ ] All handlers implemented and registered\n288: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n289: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n290: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n291: - [ ] Rollback strategy verified by tests\n292: - [ ] Integration with client-go, informers, dynamic client, Store, SandboxReconciler complete\n293: - [ ] Auth mode (EnableAuth) tested with per-user client cache\n294: - [ ] WarmPool support for CodeInterpreter verified\n295: - [ ] Timeout (2min) and rollback (30s) enforced\n296: - [ ] Pod IP resolution covers all paths (annotation, owner reference, label selector)\n297: \n298: ## Dependencies\n299: \n300: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n301: - **Required**: client-go typed clients, informers, listers operational\n302: - **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (from controller package)\n303: - **Required**: Store interface (Redis-backed) operational\n\n(End of file - total 303 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n  - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775845688977,"end":1775845688999}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845689005,"sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6c0e6001EtlBpiM0dYclVe","messageID":"msg_d78a6a34f0012yskB0YhP0Wfxa","sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_cac1199d03af4bccaa4a147d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `DeleteSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n18:   - Field: `Message` (string)\n19:   - JSON tag: `{\"message\":\"...\"}`\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `SandboxCleanupReason` type and constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n22:   - Type: `type SandboxCleanupReason string`\n23:   - Constants: `CleanupReasonManual`, `CleanupReasonIdleTimeout`, `CleanupReasonExpired`\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `CleanupAuditEntry` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n26:   - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `Namespace` (string), `Reason` (SandboxCleanupReason), `DeletedAt` (time.Time), `Success` (bool), `ErrorMessage` (string, omitempty)\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define lifecycle constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n29:   - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), `GCInterval` (15s), `GCSingleTickTimeout` (2m), `DeleteTimeout` (30s)\n30: \n31: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define label/annotation keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n32:   - Keys: `SessionIDLabelKey`, `WorkloadNameLabelKey`, `SandboxNameLabelKey`, `LastActivityAnnotationKey`, `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey`, `ManagedByLabel`\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: GarbageCollector Infrastructure\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `garbageCollector` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n37:   - Fields: `k8sClient` (*K8sClient), `storeClient` (store.Store), `interval` (time.Duration), `ctx` (context.Context), `cancel` (context.CancelFunc)\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `newGarbageCollector()` constructor\n40:   - Parameters: k8sClient, storeClient, interval\n41:   - Creates context with context.WithCancel\n42:   - Returns initialized *garbageCollector\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Start()` method for GarbageCollector\n45:   - Launches `gcLoop()` as goroutine\n46:   - Non-blocking\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Stop()` method for GarbageCollector\n49:   - Calls cancel() to signal shutdown\n50:   - Graceful termination\n51: \n52: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `gcLoop()` method\n53:   - Creates ticker with gc.interval\n54:   - Select on ctx.Done() and ticker.C\n55:   - Calls `tick()` on each tick\n56:   - Logs start/stop messages\n57: \n58: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `tick()` method\n59:   - Creates context with GCSingleTickTimeout\n60:   - Calculates idleThreshold (now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout) and expiredThreshold (now)\n61:   - Calls ListInactiveSandboxes with limit 16\n62:   - Calls ListExpiredSandboxes with limit 16\n63:   - For each sandbox, calls `deleteSandbox()` with appropriate reason\n64: \n65: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `deleteSandbox()` method\n66:   - Creates CleanupAuditEntry\n67:   - Determines GVR based on Kind (SandboxClaim vs Sandbox)\n68:   - Creates delete context with DeleteTimeout\n69:   - Calls dynamicClient.Delete\n70:   - Treats K8s NotFound as success\n71:   - Calls DeleteSandboxBySessionID on success\n72:   - Logs warning on Store delete failure (doesn't fail request)\n73:   - Calls `recordAudit()`\n74: \n75: - [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `recordAudit()` method\n76:   - Logs audit entry as info level\n77:   - Structured logging with entry fields\n78: \n79: ### Phase 3: Delete Handler\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `HandleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go`\n82:   - Extract sessionId from gin.Context.Param(\"sessionId\")\n83:   - Validate sessionId non-empty → 400 if empty\n84:   - Call store.GetSandboxBySessionID\n85:   - Handle ErrNotFound → 404 with message containing session id\n86:   - Handle other store errors → 500\n87:   - Determine GVR based on SandboxInfo.Kind\n88:   - Call dynamicClient.Delete with DeleteTimeout\n89:   - Treat K8s NotFound as success\n90:   - Call DeleteSandboxBySessionID (log warning on failure)\n91:   - Return 200 with DeleteSandboxResponse\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Register DELETE routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n94:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → HandleDeleteSandbox\n95:   - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → HandleDeleteSandbox\n96: \n97: ### Phase 4: Server Integration\n98: \n99: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Add `garbageCollector` field to `Server` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n100: \n101: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Initialize GarbageCollector in `NewServer()`\n102:   - Call `newGarbageCollector(client, store.Storage(), GCInterval)`\n103:   - Assign to server.garbageCollector\n104: \n105: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Start GarbageCollector in `Run()` method\n106:   - Call `s.garbageCollector.Start()` before HTTP server starts\n107: \n108: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Stop GarbageCollector in `Shutdown()` method\n109:   - Call `s.garbageCollector.Stop()` before HTTP shutdown\n110: \n111: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n112: \n113: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement error mapping in handler\n114:   - sessionId empty → 400 `sessionId is required`\n115:   - Store NotFound → 404 `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n116:   - Store other error → 500 `internal server error`\n117:   - K8s API error (non-NotFound) → 500 `internal server error`\n118:   - K8s NotFound → treat as success (continue to delete store record)\n119: \n120: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement rollback strategy\n121:   - K8s delete fails (non-NotFound): don't delete store record, return 500\n122:   - K8s delete succeeds but Store delete fails: log warning, don't return error\n123:   - K8s returns NotFound: continue to delete store record, return 200\n124: \n125: ### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n126: \n127: #### Unit Tests - Handler\n128: \n129: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_test.go`\n130:   - Given: session exists in store and K8s\n131:   - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n132:   - Then: 200, response contains \"Sandbox deleted successfully\"\n133:   - Verify: store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID called\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (TestCase-WM-004)\n136:   - Given: session not in store\n137:   - When: DELETE invoked\n138:   - Then: 404, message contains session id and \"not found\"\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_KubernetesNotFound`\n141:   - Given: session in store but not in K8s\n142:   - When: DELETE invoked\n143:   - Then: 200 (K8s NotFound treated as success), store record deleted\n144: \n145: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_SandboxClaim`\n146:   - Given: Kind=SandboxClaim in store\n147:   - When: DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId\n148:   - Then: 200, SandboxClaim deleted (not Sandbox)\n149: \n150: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_EmptySessionId`\n151:   - Given: sessionId is empty string\n152:   - When: DELETE invoked\n153:   - Then: 400, message contains \"sessionId is required\"\n154: \n155: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_StoreError`\n156:   - Given: store returns non-NotFound error\n157:   - When: DELETE invoked\n158:   - Then: 500, message \"internal server error\"\n159: \n160: #### Unit Tests - GarbageCollector\n161: \n162: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_IdleSandboxes` in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n163:   - Given: ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandbox\n164:   - When: tick() called\n165:   - Then: sandbox deleted from K8s and store\n166: \n167: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ExpiredSandboxes`\n168:   - Given: ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandbox\n169:   - When: tick() called\n170:   - Then: sandbox deleted from K8s and store\n171: \n172: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_KubernetesNotFound`\n173:   - Given: sandbox in store but not in K8s\n174:   - When: tick() called\n175:   - Then: store record still deleted, no error\n176: \n177: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop`\n178:   - Given: initialized GC\n179:   - When: Start() then Stop() called\n180:   - Then: gcLoop exits cleanly (no panic, context cancelled)\n181: \n182: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_BothLists`\n183:   - Given: both idle and expired sandboxes returned\n184:   - When: tick() called\n185:   - Then: all sandboxes processed, no duplicates if overlap\n186: \n187: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ListInactiveError`\n188:   - Given: ListInactiveSandboxes returns error\n189:   - When: tick() called\n190:   - Then: error logged, continues to ListExpiredSandboxes\n191: \n192: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestGarbageCollector_Tick_ListExpiredError`\n193:   - Given: ListExpiredSandboxes returns error\n194:   - When: tick() called\n195:   - Then: error logged, doesn't crash\n196: \n197: #### Test Infrastructure\n198: \n199: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `buildUnstructuredSandbox()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n200:   - Returns *unstructured.Unstructured with apiVersion, kind, metadata\n201:   - Sets required labels\n202: \n203: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Create `buildUnstructuredSandboxClaim()` helper\n204:   - Similar to above but for SandboxClaim\n205: \n206: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock store interface\n207:   - Mock Store with methods: GetSandboxBySessionID, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes\n208: \n209: #### Integration Tests\n210: \n211: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_DeleteSandbox` in `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n212:   - Deploy AgentCube (Helm to Kind)\n213:   - Create sandbox via POST /v1/agent-runtime\n214:   - Verify sandbox accessible\n215:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n216:   - Verify 200 response\n217:   - Verify sandbox deleted (GET should 404)\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestE2E_GarbageCollector_IdleTimeout`\n220:   - Create sandbox\n221:   - Wait for idle timeout (15m + GCInterval)\n222:   - Verify sandbox auto-deleted by GC\n223: \n224: - [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestE2E_GarbageCollector_Expired`\n225:   - Create sandbox with short TTL (override for test)\n226:   - Wait for expiration\n227:   - Verify sandbox auto-deleted by GC\n228: \n229: #### Coverage Verification\n230: \n231: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n232:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n233:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n234:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n235: \n236: ### Phase 7: Documentation\n237: \n238: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n239:   - Example DELETE request/response for AgentRuntime\n240:   - Example DELETE request/response for CodeInterpreter\n241: \n242: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n243:   - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n244:   - Explain K8s NotFound treated as success\n245: \n246: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Document GarbageCollector behavior\n247:   - GC interval, batch size, timeout values\n248:   - Cleanup reasons (manual/idle_timeout/expired)\n249:   - Audit logging\n250: \n251: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Add configuration options to README\n252:   - Environment variables for GC_INTERVAL, SANDBOX_TTL, IDLE_TIMEOUT\n253:   - Default values and recommended ranges\n254: \n255: ## Acceptance Criteria\n256: \n257: - [ ] Delete handler implemented for both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n258: - [ ] GarbageCollector implemented with idle and expired cleanup\n259: - [ ] All handlers and GC routes registered\n260: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n261: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n262: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n263: - [ ] K8s NotFound treated as success (verified by tests)\n264: - [ ] Store delete failures logged as warnings (not returned to client)\n265: - [ ] GC runs every 15s with 2m tick timeout\n266: - [ ] GC batch size 16 for both idle and expired lists\n267: - [ ] Audit logging for all GC deletions\n268: - [ ] Server properly starts/stops GC lifecycle\n269: - [ ] Integration with Store (Get/Delete/List) verified\n270: - [ ] Integration with dynamic client (Delete) verified\n271: \n272: ## Dependencies\n273: \n274: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n275: - **Required**: Store interface operational (GetSandboxBySessionID, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes)\n276: - **Required**: dynamic client configured for Sandbox/SandboxClaim GVR\n277: - **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (for watcher cleanup on delete)\n\n(End of file - total 277 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `DeleteSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n  - Field: `Message` (string)\n  - JSON tag: `{\"message\":\"...\"}`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-006-sandbox-deletion-lifecycle/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775845688979,"end":1775845689003}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845689007,"sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6b02d0018TlQ0IhWaB8MS1","messageID":"msg_d78a6a34f0012yskB0YhP0Wfxa","sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a5a8f4162a504cf286657e04","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Implement Kubernetes reconciler controller for workload management in the pkg/workloadmanager module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Design reconciler architecture\n15: - [ ] Implement reconciler core logic\n16: - [ ] Add status management\n17: - [ ] Implement error handling and retry logic\n18: - [ ] Add unit tests\n19: - [ ] Add integration tests\n20: \n21: ## Notes\n22: \n23: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n24: \n25: ## Source Files\n26: \n27: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement Kubernetes reconciler controller for workload management in the pkg/workloadmanager module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Design reconciler architecture\n- [ ] Implement reconciler core logic\n- [ ] Add status management\n- [ ] Implement error handling and retry logic\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-codi