{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775845692831,"sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6d59d00126v6oHojQj5iGm","messageID":"msg_d78a6c6f60010vzhTyYyjV1Pc5","sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845798130,"sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","part":{"id":"prt_d78a6d8b5001MdAw5nzs8p2LvM","messageID":"msg_d78a6c6f60010vzhTyYyjV1Pc5","sessionID":"ses_2875971e6ffeIxBNdiOINqBuQE","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2f95625be92a41f8bd334743","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n  - Document each method purpose\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `Request` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Fields: `Namespace` (string), `Name` (string)\n  - Document usage in reconciliation loop\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `Result` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Fields: `Requeue` (bool), `RequeueAfter` (time.Duration)\n  - Document requeue behavior and priorities\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `ReconcilerConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Fields: `ResyncPeriod`, `MaxRetries`, `RateLimitQPS`, `RateLimitBurst`, `ConcurrentReconciles`, `EnableLeaderElection`, `LeaderElectionNamespace`, `LeaderElectionName`\n  - All fields documented with comments\n\n- [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `DefaultReconcilerConfig()` function\n  - Returns default configuration per design spec\n  - Defaults: ResyncPeriod=10m, MaxRetries=5, RateLimitQPS=10, RateLimitBurst=20, ConcurrentReconciles=2\n\n- [ ] **TASK-006**: Define error constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n  - Constants: `ErrReconcileFailed`, `ErrPodCreationFailed`, `ErrPodUpdateFailed`, `ErrStatusUpdateFailed`, `ErrOwnerRefFailed`, `ErrCacheMiss`, `ErrInvalidSpec`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ReconcileError` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n  - Fields: `Type` (string), `Message` (string), `Err` (error), `Retryable` (bool)\n  - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-008**: Implement `IsRetryableError()` function\n  - Checks `*ReconcileError.Retryable`\n  - Checks k8s transient errors: `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests`, `IsServerTimeout`\n\n### Phase 2: ControllerManager Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ControllerManager` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `informerFactory`, `reconcilers`, `ctx`, `cancel`\n  - Informer fields: `agentRuntimeInformer`, `codeInterpreterInformer`, `podInformer`\n  - Lister fields: `agentRuntimeLister`, `codeInterpreterLister`, `podLister`\n  - Event recorder: `recorder`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewControllerManager()` constructor\n  - Creates versioned clientset and kubernetes clientset\n  - Initializes SharedInformerFactory with 10m resync\n  - Returns initialized *ControllerManager or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `AddReconciler()` method\n  - Appends reconciler to manager's reconcilers slice\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `SetupInformers()` method\n  - Gets typed informers from factory\n  - Returns error if setup fails\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `StartInformers()` method\n  - Starts informer factory\n  - Waits for cache sync with timeout\n  - Verifies critical informers synced (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod)\n  - Gets listers from informers\n\n- [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `Start()` method\n  - Starts informers\n  - Waits for cache sync\n  - Starts all reconcilers as goroutines\n  - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n  - Handles graceful shutdown (workqueue drain)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement graceful shutdown in `Start()`\n  - Shuts down workqueues\n  - Waits for workqueue.Done()\n  - Logs shutdown progress\n\n### Phase 3: AgentRuntimeReconciler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `AgentRuntimeReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go`\n  - Fields: `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `lister`, `podLister`, `recorder`, `workqueue`, `metrics`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewAgentRuntimeReconciler()` constructor\n  - Creates reconciler with rate-limiting workqueue\n  - Registers event handlers on AgentRuntime informer\n  - Registers event handlers on Pod informer (for owned pods)\n  - Returns initialized *AgentRuntimeReconciler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `Run()` method for AgentRuntimeReconciler\n  - Creates context from stopCh\n  - Starts reconciliation workers (ConcurrentReconciles workers)\n  - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n  - Fetches AgentRuntime from lister\n  - Handles NotFound (skip reconciliation)\n  - Handles deletion (calls `reconcileDeletion()`)\n  - Reconciles sandbox pod (calls `reconcileSandboxPod()`)\n  - Updates status (calls `updateStatus()`)\n  - Records events and metrics\n  - Returns Result with requeue logic\n\n- [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method\n  - Handles finalizer cleanup\n  - Deletes owned sandbox pod\n  - Removes finalizer\n  - Returns Result\n\n- [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method\n  - Checks if pod exists (from lister cache)\n  - If not found: builds and creates new pod\n  - If exists: checks if update needed\n  - If needs update: delete-and-recreate\n  - Returns pod or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement event handler methods\n  - `enqueueObject(obj interface{})` - casts to AgentRuntime, enqueues Request\n  - `enqueueUpdate(old, new interface{})` - handles updates\n  - `enqueueDelete(obj interface{})` - handles deletions\n  - `enqueueOwnedPod(obj interface{})` - finds owner, enqueues AgentRuntime\n  - `enqueueOwnedPodUpdate(old, new interface{})`\n  - `enqueueOwnedPodDelete(obj interface{})`\n\n### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterReconciler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `CodeInterpreterReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go`\n  - Fields: same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCodeInterpreterReconciler()` constructor\n  - Same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n  - Registers event handlers on CodeInterpreter informer\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Run()` method for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n\n- [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n  - Same reconciliation pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n  - Handles CodeInterpreter CRD\n\n- [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method for CodeInterpreter\n\n- [ ] **TASK-035**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n  - Builds pod from CodeInterpreter spec\n  - Same create/update/delete pattern\n\n- [ ] **TASK-036**: Implement event handler methods for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n\n### Phase 5: SandboxProcessor\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `SandboxProcessor` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor.go`\n  - Fields: `k8sClient`, `scheme`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `NewSandboxProcessor()` constructor\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `BuildSandboxPod()` method for AgentRuntime\n  - Creates Pod with name `sandbox-{ar.Name}`\n  - Sets labels: `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime`, `agentcube.volcano.sh/type`\n  - Builds PodSpec from AgentRuntime spec\n  - Sets owner reference\n  - Returns *corev1.Pod or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `buildPodSpec()` helper method\n  - Builds container spec from `ar.Spec.Container`\n  - Sets Resources, Ports, VolumeMounts\n  - Sets RestartPolicy=Never\n  - Sets SecurityContext, Affinity, Tolerations\n  - Adds code interpreter sidecar if enabled\n\n- [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `BuildSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n  - Similar to AgentRuntime but from CodeInterpreter spec\n\n- [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `NeedsUpdate()` method\n  - Checks if container image changed\n  - Checks if resources changed\n  - Checks if environment variables changed\n  - Returns bool\n\n- [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `UpdateSandboxPod()` method\n  - Deletes existing pod\n  - Waits for deletion (using wait.PollUntilContextTimeout)\n  - Creates new pod\n  - Returns *corev1.Pod or error\n\n- [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement helper functions\n  - `buildEnvFrom()` - converts env vars\n  - `buildResourceRequirements()` - converts resource quotas\n  - `buildContainerPorts()` - converts network spec\n  - `buildVolumeMounts()` and `buildVolumes()`\n  - `buildPodSecurityContext()`\n  - `buildAffinity()` and `buildTolerations()`\n  - `buildCodeInterpreterContainer()` - builds sidecar container\n\n### Phase 6: StatusUpdater\n\n- [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `StatusUpdater` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater.go`\n  - Field: `clientset`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `NewStatusUpdater()` constructor\n\n- [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus()` method\n  - Creates deep copy of AgentRuntime\n  - Sets Phase based on pod state\n  - Sets SandboxRef\n  - Builds Conditions from pod\n  - Updates Endpoint if pod running\n  - Skips update if status unchanged\n  - Calls UpdateStatus subresource\n\n- [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus()` method\n  - Same pattern as AgentRuntime\n\n- [ ] **TASK-054**: Implement `mapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase()` function\n  - Maps PodPhase to AgentRuntimePhase/CodeInterpreterPhase\n  - Handles: Pending, Running, Failed, Succeeded, Unknown\n\n- [ ] **TASK-055**: Implement `buildConditionsFromPod()` function\n  - Converts PodConditions to CRD Conditions\n\n- [ ] **TASK-056**: Implement `buildEndpointFromPod()` function\n  - Builds endpoint URL from PodIP and container port\n\n### Phase 7: OwnerReference Management\n\n- [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `SetControllerReference()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference.go`\n  - Uses `metav1.NewControllerRef()`\n  - Sets owner reference on child object\n\n- [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `IsOwnedBy()` function\n  - Checks if object has owner reference with matching UID and Controller=true\n\n- [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `GetControllerOf()` helper\n  - Returns controller owner reference if exists\n\n### Phase 8: Metrics\n\n- [ ] **TASK-070**: Implement `ReconcilerMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics.go`\n  - Fields: `reconcileDuration` (Histogram), `reconcileErrors` (Counter), `reconcileTotal` (Counter), `workqueueDepth` (Gauge), `workqueueLatency` (Histogram)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement `NewReconcilerMetrics()` constructor\n  - Creates Prometheus metrics with proper naming\n  - Registers metrics if registerer provided\n\n- [ ] **TASK-072**: Implement metric methods\n  - `observeReconcileDuration(d time.Duration)`\n  - `recordError(errorType string)`\n  - `recordReconcile()`\n\n### Phase 9: Error Handling & Retry Logic\n\n- [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement centralized error handling in Reconcile methods\n  - Logs errors with context\n  - Records metrics\n  - Records events\n  - Determines retryability\n\n- [ ] **TASK-081**: Implement `calculateBackoff()` function\n  - Exponential backoff: baseDelay * 2^retryCount\n  - Max delay: 5 minutes\n  - Adds jitter (±20%)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-082**: Handle k8s error types per design spec\n  - `IsNotFound` - skip reconciliation\n  - `IsAlreadyExists` - check if update needed\n  - `IsConflict` - re-fetch and retry\n  - `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests` - exponential backoff\n\n### Phase 10: Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-090**: Add reconciler flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n  - Flags: `--reconciler-resync-period`, `--reconciler-max-retries`, `--reconciler-rate-limit-qps`, `--reconciler-rate-limit-burst`, `--reconciler-concurrent`, `--reconciler-leader-election`, `--reconciler-leader-election-namespace`, `--reconciler-leader-election-name`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-091**: Integrate reconciler with main startup\n  - Load config\n  - Create ControllerManager\n  - Create reconcilers\n  - Add reconcilers to manager\n  - Start manager\n\n- [ ] **TASK-092**: Document environment variables\n  - `RECONCILER_RESYNC_PERIOD`, `RECONCILER_MAX_RETRIES`, `RECONCILER_RATE_LIMIT_QPS`, `RECONCILER_RATE_LIMIT_BURST`, `RECONCILER_CONCURRENT`, `RECONCILER_LEADER_ELECTION`, etc.\n\n### Phase 11: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - Reconciler\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_Success` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler_test.go`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime in informer cache\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: Pod created, no error, no requeue\n  - Use fake clientset + fake k8s client + mock informers\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_PodExists`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with existing owned pod\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: No new pod created, status updated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_NeedsUpdate`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with changed spec\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: Pod deleted and recreated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_Deletion`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp set\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: Pod deleted, finalizer removed\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound`\n  - Given: Non-existent AgentRuntime\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: No error, no requeue\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_PodCreationFailed`\n  - Given: Invalid pod spec\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: Error returned, event recorded, retry scheduled\n\n- [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_StatusUpdateFailed`\n  - Given: Pod created but status update fails\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: Error returned, event recorded, retry scheduled\n\n- [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Reconcile_Success`\n  - Same pattern as AgentRuntime tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Reconcile_WithSidecar`\n  - Given: CodeInterpreter with code interpreter enabled\n  - When: Reconcile() called\n  - Then: Pod created with sidecar container\n\n#### Unit Tests - SandboxProcessor\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestSandboxProcessor_BuildSandboxPod` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with full spec\n  - When: BuildSandboxPod() called\n  - Then: Pod has correct name, labels, owner reference, container spec\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestSandboxProcessor_BuildSandboxPod_WithCodeInterpreter`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with CodeInterpreter enabled\n  - When: BuildSandboxPod() called\n  - Then: Pod has sidecar container\n\n- [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestSandboxProcessor_NeedsUpdate_ImageChanged`\n  - Given: Pod with old image, AgentRuntime with new image\n  - When: NeedsUpdate() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestSandboxProcessor_NeedsUpdate_NoChange`\n  - Given: Pod matches AgentRuntime spec\n  - When: NeedsUpdate() called\n  - Then: Returns false\n\n- [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestSandboxProcessor_UpdateSandboxPod`\n  - Given: Pod needs update\n  - When: UpdateSandboxPod() called\n  - Then: Old pod deleted, new pod created\n\n#### Unit Tests - StatusUpdater\n\n- [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodRunning` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater_test.go`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with running pod\n  - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n  - Then: Status.Phase=Running, SandboxRef set, Endpoint set\n\n- [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodPending`\n  - Given: AgentRuntime with pending pod\n  - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n  - Then: Status.Phase=Pending\n\n- [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_NoChange`\n  - Given: Status unchanged\n  - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n  - Then: No API call made\n\n- [ ] **TEST-018**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus_PodRunning`\n  - Same pattern for CodeInterpreter\n\n#### Unit Tests - OwnerReference\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestSetControllerReference` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference_test.go`\n  - Given: Owner and child objects\n  - When: SetControllerReference() called\n  - Then: Child has owner reference with Controller=true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestIsOwnedBy_True`\n  - Given: Object with matching owner reference\n  - When: IsOwnedBy() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-022**: `TestIsOwnedBy_False`\n  - Given: Object with different owner\n  - When: IsOwnedBy() called\n  - Then: Returns false\n\n#### Unit Tests - Error Handling\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestIsRetryableError_True` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors_test.go`\n  - Given: Timeout, TooManyRequests errors\n  - When: IsRetryableError() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestIsRetryableError_False`\n  - Given: NotFound, InvalidSpec errors\n  - When: IsRetryableError() called\n  - Then: Returns false\n\n- [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestCalculateBackoff`\n  - Given: Various retry counts\n  - When: calculateBackoff() called\n  - Then: Returns exponentially increasing delays with jitter\n\n#### Unit Tests - Metrics\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: `TestReconcilerMetrics_ObserveReconcileDuration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics_test.go`\n  - Given: Metrics registered\n  - When: observeReconcileDuration() called\n  - Then: Histogram updated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: `TestReconcilerMetrics_RecordError`\n  - Given: Metrics registered\n  - When: recordError() called\n  - Then: Counter incremented\n\n#### Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: Create `newTestReconciler()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler_test.go`\n  - Creates fake clientset, fake k8s client, informers, recorder\n  - Returns initialized reconciler for testing\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: Create `newTestControllerManager()` helper\n  - Uses envtest for integration tests\n  - Returns ControllerManager with teardown function\n\n- [ ] **TEST-052**: Create mock implementations\n  - Mock Reconciler interface\n  - Mock metrics interface\n\n- [ ] **TEST-053**: Create test fixtures\n  - `buildAgentRuntime()` - creates test AgentRuntime objects\n  - `buildCodeInterpreter()` - creates test CodeInterpreter objects\n  - `buildPod()` - creates test Pod objects\n  - `buildPodWithStatus()` - creates pods with specific status\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-060**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Integration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/integration_test.go`\n  - Use envtest to start real K8s API server\n  - Create CRD\n  - Create AgentRuntime\n  - Trigger reconciliation\n  - Verify pod created\n  - Verify status updated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-061**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Integration`\n  - Same pattern for CodeInterpreter\n\n- [ ] **TEST-062**: `TestControllerManager_StartStop`\n  - Create ControllerManager\n  - Start manager\n  - Wait for cache sync\n  - Stop manager\n  - Verify graceful shutdown\n\n#### Coverage Verification\n\n- [ ] **TEST-070**: Run coverage check\n  - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n  - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.5\n  - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n  - Verify all reconciliation paths covered\n\n### Phase 12: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/doc.go`\n  - Package overview\n  - Architecture description\n  - Usage example\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n  - Document parameters, return values\n  - Document error conditions\n  - Include examples where applicable\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Document reconciliation loop in code comments\n  - Step-by-step flow\n  - Error handling strategy\n  - Retry behavior\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md`\n  - Add reconciler architecture section\n  - Include component diagram\n  - Document configuration options\n  - List environment variables\n\n- [ ] **DOC-005**: Add API contracts documentation\n  - Reconciliation contract\n  - Owner reference pattern\n  - Status update contract\n  - Event recording\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] ControllerManager implemented with proper lifecycle management\n- [ ] AgentRuntimeReconciler implemented with full reconciliation loop\n- [ ] CodeInterpreterReconciler implemented with full reconciliation loop\n- [ ] SandboxProcessor builds pods from both CRD types\n- [ ] StatusUpdater updates CRD status based on pod state\n- [ ] Owner reference management ensures proper garbage collection\n- [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n- [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n- [ ] Retry logic with exponential backoff implemented\n- [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n- [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented and tested\n- [ ] Integration with client-go informers and listers verified\n- [ ] Workqueue rate limiting functional\n- [ ] Events recorded for significant reconciliation actions\n- [ ] Configuration via flags and environment variables\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (client-go typed clients, informers, listers)\n- **Required**: CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) registered and served\n- **Required**: RBAC permissions for watching CRDs and managing Pods\n- **Required**: SharedInformerFactory operational\n- **Related**: AR-004 (HTTP server) - reconciler runs alongside HTTP server\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_baili